[Attaching a fix. This is slightly different from what I suggested above. Because a result needs to be returned for the future, I've added an unknownError field to the results that the futures check. If there is an error, the futures call registerError., Adding a better patch. The problem was in the error handling. The calling thread waits for the operation to succeed or until signaled that unknownError is set. When an error is passed to signal that thread, there's a check for whether another error has already been set, but the check is wrong. It only sets the error if another error is already set, rather than if no other error has been set. The result is that if there is an error, the caller is never signaled and waits indefinitely for all of the tasks to complete successfully., [~rkanter], can you take a look at this?, | (x) *{color:red}-1 overall{color}* |
